Class.name: Administrative category code (NHS DD)
Class.description:
This is recorded for PATIENT ACTIVITY.

A PATIENT who is an Overseas Visitor does not qualify for free NHS healthcare and can choose to pay for NHS treatment or for private treatment. If they pay for NHS treatment then they should be recorded as NHS PATIENTS.

The PATIENT's ADMINISTRATIVE CATEGORY CODE may change during an episode or spell. For example, the PATIENT may opt to change from NHS to private health care. In this case, the start and end dates for each new ADMINISTRATIVE CATEGORY PERIOD (episode or spell) should be recorded.

If the ADMINISTRATIVE CATEGORY CODE changes during a Hospital Provider Spell the ADMINISTRATIVE CATEGORY CODE (ON ADMISSION) is used to derive the 'Category of PATIENT' for Hospital Episode Statistics (HES).

The category 'amenity PATIENT' is only applicable to PATIENTS using a Hospital Bed.

ObjectProperty.name: data model display property
ObjectProperty.description: A property that points to the display algorithm for this particular entity

ObjectProperty.name: method (attribute)
ObjectProperty.description: Snomed method attribute - 260686004

ObjectProperty.name: data model derived property
ObjectProperty.description: A data model property that is derived only when the record is examined. The properties value is generated via  function which takes a number of parameters, including other property values from the record

ObjectProperty.name: administrative category (NHS DD)
ObjectProperty.description: points to the patient administrative category at time of admission

ObjectProperty.name: used
ObjectProperty.description:
A provenance property indicating that something was used.
it is the beginning of utilizing an entity by an activity.

ObjectProperty.name: has admission method
ObjectProperty.description: Points to the method of admission such as whether from waiting list, booked or from A&e or direct from GP

ObjectProperty.name: is child code of
ObjectProperty.description: the code on the left is a child code of the code on the right in a legacy classification

ObjectProperty.name: has organisation type
ObjectProperty.description: points to the type of organisation

ObjectProperty.name: has attendance outcome
ObjectProperty.description: points to the outcome of the attendance

ObjectProperty.name: is subject of
ObjectProperty.description: references the entries that this object is the subject of e.g. Patient 'is subject of' Encounter

ObjectProperty.name: has arrival mode
ObjectProperty.description: points to the mode of arrival in accident and emergency

ObjectProperty.name: is component of
ObjectProperty.description: the entity is part of another entity e.g. a parent observation

ObjectProperty.name: was generated by
ObjectProperty.description: An entity was generated by a provenance activity

ObjectProperty.name: dependent relationship
ObjectProperty.description:
A dependent relationship is where the source entity depends on the presence of the target entity to exist i.e. is a component of it or some business process requires it. 
An example of this is that a hospital admission encounter is dependent on an inpatient stay encounter

ObjectProperty.name: on care classification
ObjectProperty.description: points to the classification of care the patient is on whilst activity is being performed e.g. on waiting list

ObjectProperty.name: is subsection of
ObjectProperty.description: A section is a subsection of another section

ObjectProperty.name: is provenance for
ObjectProperty.description: points to the record entry that this is the provenance for

ObjectProperty.name: has type
ObjectProperty.description:
The type of this record entry or directory entry which may further qualifier the properties of the entry.
The property points to a value set which is increasingly specific with sub types of record entries or directory entries

ObjectProperty.name: from care classification
ObjectProperty.description: points to the preceding care classification in a transfer

ObjectProperty.name: has participants
ObjectProperty.description: The type of people the encounter took place between e.g. the patient and health professiona;, third party and health professional, team etc

ObjectProperty.name: is under heading of
ObjectProperty.description: points to the record or encounter section heading that this component is part of

ObjectProperty.name: has admission source
ObjectProperty.description: Points to the source of admission of the patient

ObjectProperty.name: responsible Practitioner
ObjectProperty.description: sub property of health event responsible agent, pointing to a practitioner

ObjectProperty.name: generated
ObjectProperty.description: An activity generated an entity of some kind

ObjectProperty.name: has subject
ObjectProperty.description: points to the patient this record is about

ObjectProperty.name: has admission classification of patient
ObjectProperty.description: Points to the admissin classification of a patient e.g. elective day admission or non elective ordinay admission of maternity

ObjectProperty.name: has discharge destination
ObjectProperty.description: pints to the type of place a patient was discharged to

ObjectProperty.name: has critical care unit function
ObjectProperty.description: Points to the overall function of the critical care unit

ObjectProperty.name: has replaced
ObjectProperty.description: the newer concept on the left has replaced the older concept on the right

ObjectProperty.name: responsible agent
ObjectProperty.description:
High level property indicating the person responsible for the event,if the event is a recording of something seen, done, thought or measured.
This is an abstract property which is specialised in the data model for the particular health entries.
Implementation schema maps can map at this level in order to have one field throughout the data base (e.g. agent or user) to mean the same thing

ObjectProperty.name: was performed by
ObjectProperty.description: references the person or device that performed the activity,usually used in provvenance

ObjectProperty.name: treatment function for service for which admitted
ObjectProperty.description: Treatment function / speciality service for which admitted

ObjectProperty.name: replaced with (or by)
ObjectProperty.description: A concept on the left has been replaced by another concept on the right

ObjectProperty.name: Entity sub type attribute
ObjectProperty.description: Points to the field in the implmented database scheme which is used as the subtype indicator during query or fiing of data

ObjectProperty.name: administrative category
ObjectProperty.description: points to patient administrative category for payment purposes

ObjectProperty.name: has a&e category of attendance of
ObjectProperty.description: points to the category of attendance whether first, subsequent, planned or unplanned

ObjectProperty.name: was associated with
ObjectProperty.description: usually used in provenance to associate an activity or entity with an agent

ObjectProperty.name: has provenance
ObjectProperty.description: references the provenence of an entry i.e the history of the entry or its contents going back to its original creation

ObjectProperty.name: has observation type
ObjectProperty.description: points to the main observation concept e.g. pulse rate, asthma

ObjectProperty.name: is data controller for
ObjectProperty.description: References the entry that the organisation is data controller of. Inverse property of 'has data controller'

ObjectProperty.name: has activity
ObjectProperty.description: references the activity relevant to the item e.g. a provenance activity

ObjectProperty.name: to care classification
ObjectProperty.description: points to the subsequent care classification of the patient e.g. to inpatient

ObjectProperty.name: is part of encounter
ObjectProperty.description: points to the encounter this is part of

ObjectProperty.name: is a record of
ObjectProperty.description:
Points to the 'type of entry' that a health record entry is a record of.
For example, an encounter (entry) may nbe a record of a 'GP surgery consultation'. A hospital admission entry is a record of a 'Hospital admission'

ObjectProperty.name: has resource locator type
ObjectProperty.description: the nature of the resource location e.g. URL, IRI, domain, directory etc

ObjectProperty.name: has record held by
ObjectProperty.description: relationship pointing to the organisaion that holds the record for patient or client

ObjectProperty.name: has time aspect
ObjectProperty.description: points to a time period type such as night time or day time

ObjectProperty.name: has attendance status
ObjectProperty.description: points to whether the patient attended or not

ObjectProperty.name: is process
ObjectProperty.description: points to a type of care administration process such as an admission discharge or administration note

ObjectProperty.name: acted on behalf of
ObjectProperty.description:
An agent acting on behalf of another agent or organisation.
tHE the assignment of authority and responsibility to an agent (by itself or by another agent) to carry out a specific activity as a delegate or representative, while the agent it acts on behalf of retains some responsibility for the outcome of the delegated work.

ObjectProperty.name: has discharge method
ObjectProperty.description: ponts to the method of discharge of the patient

ObjectProperty.name: was attributed to
ObjectProperty.description: The ascribing of an entity to an agent.

ObjectProperty.name: has crud operation
ObjectProperty.description: create read update and delete operations to the data store

ObjectProperty.name: data model object property
ObjectProperty.description: A property that would be used in the data store  as a table field) as opposed to a property that is part of the definition of the class and points to an object (concept) or other entity (foreign key)

ObjectProperty.name: has a&e attendance source of
ObjectProperty.description: points to the attendance source type for an a&E visit

ObjectProperty.name: treatment function type
ObjectProperty.description: points to a treatment specialty service type

ObjectProperty.name: is entry class
ObjectProperty.description: a tautoligical property indicating that the object is an entry as stored in a database. Its use is to indicate to implementors who are using high level entity types, as to the nature of the content of the entry i.e. the archetype

ObjectProperty.name: has event type of
ObjectProperty.description: references the concept that describes the type of event

ObjectProperty.name: was derived from
ObjectProperty.description: references a resource from which the resource or entry was transformed from

ObjectProperty.name: data model relationship
ObjectProperty.description:
A relationship between one entity and another (node to node in graph terms) where the entities are instantiated as complex objects in the data store.
For example, a reference to a colour or disease would be a data model object property, but the relationship between a patient and  health event would be a relationship sub property

ObjectProperty.name: has member
ObjectProperty.description:
A property of a value set indicating that the members of the classes are members of the value set.
This is a property abstraction to prevent value sets being a subclass of the superclasses that are its members.

ObjectProperty.name: has data controller
ObjectProperty.description: references the organisation that is the data controller of the record entry (or sub organisation of that data controller)

ObjectProperty.name: using device
ObjectProperty.description: a device used by a procedure or observation or encounter

ObjectProperty.name: takes place in care setting
ObjectProperty.description: points to a care setting.

ObjectProperty.name: has care event type
ObjectProperty.description: Points to the overall or main nature of the entry, usually a business process or observable concept of some kind e.g. an Encounter -> type -> Telephone consultation, or observation ->type-> Chest pain

ObjectProperty.name: has patient care classification
ObjectProperty.description: Points to a category of the patient/ person at the time of the event e.g. patient outpatient, inpatient

ObjectProperty.name: has heading
ObjectProperty.description: Points to the structured heading for this section

ObjectProperty.name: operates within the sector of
ObjectProperty.description: Indicates which sector the speciality works in

ObjectProperty.name: has component
ObjectProperty.description: Entity may contain subcomponents

ObjectProperty.name: has time order
ObjectProperty.description: points to the order of something relative to something else e.g. initial subsequent following etc

ObjectProperty.name: a&e department type
ObjectProperty.description: points to the type of a&e department

DataProperty.name: numeric property
DataProperty.description: A data property that has a floating point value

DataProperty.name: has Date and time of entry
DataProperty.description: A date and time a particular entry or component was made (local time)

DataProperty.name: has ODS code
DataProperty.description: holds the ODS code of the organisation

DataProperty.name: end date/time
DataProperty.description: the effective end date/time relevant to the event being described

DataProperty.name: has NHS number
DataProperty.description: property that points to the NHS number and has an NHS scheme annotation property

DataProperty.name: has component date
DataProperty.description: the date and time of the creation or update to the component

DataProperty.name: boolean property
DataProperty.description: A data property that has a true false value

DataProperty.name: has update time
DataProperty.description: date and time of the update

DataProperty.name: id
DataProperty.description:
A logical id of an entity. 
This should not be confused with a DB id (although may be mapped to a DBID in the implementation map  in some cases). This is used where the id of an entity is unique e.g. a URL/ IRI, UUID.
This is also different from a business 'has_Identifier' which are usually codes or personal identifier such as NHS numbers

DataProperty.name: has identifier
DataProperty.description: property that holds an identifier. sub properties have annotations that indicate the idenfifier scheme

DataProperty.name: data model derived property
DataProperty.description: A data model data property that is derived only when the record is examined. The properties value is generated via  function which takes a number of parameters, including other property values from the record

DataProperty.name: display order
DataProperty.description: order of display for this entity in relation to sibling entities

DataProperty.name: integer property
DataProperty.description: A property that has an integer value

DataProperty.name: date time property
DataProperty.description: A data property that has a date and time as a value

DataProperty.name: start date/time
DataProperty.description: The effective start date and time relevant to the event being described (and not related to the entry date into the system)

DataProperty.name: data model data property
DataProperty.description: indicates that this property would be expected to be implmented as a field in a database or attribute within the data store, as opposed to a definitional property in the knowledge base. It has a simple data type as a value

DataProperty.name: has name
DataProperty.description: points to the name of something such as an organisation or location with a simple form

AnnotationProperty.name: has iri
AnnotationProperty.description: property that has a universal identifier as its value, reserved property

AnnotationProperty.name: code
AnnotationProperty.description: the original or authored code for this concept
